output.crosstab_text:
For first degree graduates of Allied health, one year after graduation, Human health and social work activities was the most common industry for White, Black, Mixed, Other and Not known ethnicity graduates, and Wholesale and retail trade - repair of motor vehicles and motorcycles was the most common industry for Asian ethnicity graduates.

The industry with the largest range in proportions was Wholesale and retail trade - repair of motor vehicles and motorcycles where Asian ethnicity graduates had the highest proportion and White ethnicity graduates had the lowest proportion. The industry with the largest range in median earnings was Accommodation and food service activities where White ethnicity graduates had the highest median earnings (£14,200) and Asian ethnicity graduates had the lowest median earnings (£ 9,500). The group with the highest earnings was Mixed ethnicity graduates who worked in the Human health and social work activities industry (median earnings of £25,900).
output.crosstab_title: Industry of graduate employment for graduates of Allied health by ethnicity, one year after graduation, male and female first degree graduates from HE providers, 2020/21 tax year.
